
Architecture
Overview

This folder contains the high-level architecture and solution design artifacts for the AI-Assisted Ticket Workflow Management System.

The architecture provides a blueprint of how users, workflows, AI services, integrations, reporting components, and monitoring capabilities interact to deliver an intelligent ticket management experience.

Purpose

The objective of the architecture documentation is to:

Define the overall system structure
Illustrate component interactions
Identify integration points
Describe AI workflow processing
Support scalability and maintainability
Provide technical guidance for implementation
Architecture Scope

The architecture covers:

Ticket Management Workflow
AI Classification and Prediction Services
Workflow Automation Components
Integration Interfaces
Reporting and Dashboard Layer
Monitoring and Governance Components
Data Storage and Processing
Key Components
User Layer

Business users, support agents, managers, and administrators interacting with the system.

Workflow Engine

Manages ticket lifecycle, routing, approvals, escalations, and automation processes.

AI Services

Provides intelligent capabilities such as:

Ticket categorization
Priority prediction
SLA risk prediction
Agent recommendations
Ticket summarization
Reporting Layer

Provides operational dashboards, KPI tracking, and management reporting.

Monitoring Layer

Tracks system health, AI performance, model accuracy, and operational metrics.

Objectives
Ensure architectural clarity
Support future scalability
Enable seamless integration
Improve maintainability
Establish a foundation for AI-driven operations
Outcome

A well-defined architecture ensures that business requirements, product capabilities, AI services, and operational processes work together in a scalable, reliable, and maintainable solution.
